I really enjoyed the progression of how the Foundation figured this out. It's always so much better to have the reader follow the train of thought and come to a conclusion with them rather than just telling them. I also thought the way that the Foundation communicated with it was clever and the last interview was both well-done and builds the universe through a former Foundation employee. Well done!








Whether you like it or not, history is on our side. We will bury you!






